                            <comment id="13846891" author="nezihyigitbasi" created="Thu, 12 Dec 2013 23:16:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Guys, I plan to implement a solution that checks for an hbase prefix (&quot;hbase://&quot;) in the fileSpec variable (see FileLocalizer.delete), but this method currently uses the DataStorage interfaces (either local or distributed) kept in PigContext to access the backend storage and as far as I can see there is no HBase specific implementation for the DataStorage interface. So what do you guys think is the right way to fix this issue? Is it implementing a DataStorage interface for HBase or simply use HBaseAdmin.deleteTable to delete the temp table?&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="13858265" author="cheolsoo" created="Sun, 29 Dec 2013 07:15:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nezihyigitbasi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nezihyigitbasi&quot;&gt;Nezih Yigitbasi&lt;/a&gt;, sorry for the late reply.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see why you propose implementing a DataStorage interface for HBase, but that sounds like an overkill for this problem. Do you think that will be useful in the future for other things?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition, how about handling an hbase prefix in MapReduceLauncher rather than in FileLocalizer? &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3592&quot; title=&quot;Should not try to create success file for non-fs schemes like hbase&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3592&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3592&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes a similar issue, and it does in MapReducerLauncher. I think it is better to do storage-specific things in Launcher than in FileLocalizer because the latter currently assumes file system.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Feel free to disagree with me. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13863160" author="nezihyigitbasi" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2014 17:55:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cheolsoo, thanks for the reply. I also think that implementing a DataStorage interface for HBase is an overkill. So I implemented a simple fix to skip HBase paths during temporary file deletions in MapReduceLauncher like you proposed. Please review.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13866041" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 8 Jan 2014 23:23:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nezihyigitbasi&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nezihyigitbasi&quot;&gt;Nezih Yigitbasi&lt;/a&gt;, thank you very much for the patch. It looks good, but can I make a minor suggestion?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How about using Utils.hasFileSystemImpl() instead of checking whether a path starts with &quot;hbase&quot;? I think this approach is better because then other non-filesystem storages such as accumulo will also be protected from the same problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3617&quot; title=&quot;problem with temp file deletion in MAPREDUCE operator&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3617&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3617&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-2.patch implements what I describe here. I can commit it if you agree. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13866073" author="nezihyigitbasi" created="Wed, 8 Jan 2014 23:47:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that&apos;s even better! Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13866120" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 9 Jan 2014 00:40:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk. Thank you Nezih!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13932015" author="rohini" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2014 17:08:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just found out that with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-7549&quot; title=&quot;Use JDK ServiceLoader mechanism to find FileSystem implementations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-7549&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-7549&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in hadoop-2 branch, Utils.hasFileSystemImpl() is broken. Will open a jira to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13932081" author="nezihyigitbasi" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2014 17:58:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Aha, good catch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13932161" author="rohini" created="Wed, 12 Mar 2014 18:42:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will fix that as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3672&quot; title=&quot;Pig should not check for hardcoded file system implementations&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3672&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3672&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
